# Next.js MCP Quality Gates

Use `next-devtools` MCP (`.cursor/mcp.json`) for all `apps/app` work. Skill: `.cursor/skills/xforge-nextjs-vercel/SKILL.md`

## MUST (from MCP `init` contract)

1. **Call MCP `init` first** each session — `project_path` = absolute path to **`apps/app`** (not repo root)
2. **Forget training-data Next.js** — every API/routing/cache/Server Action question → `nextjs_docs`
3. **Read `nextjs-docs://llms-index`** before calling `nextjs_docs` — never guess doc paths
4. **`nextjs_index` before `nextjs_call`** — discover port, tools, and input schemas
5. **Resolve `get_errors` before claiming done** when dev server is available (port **3000**)

## Session workflow

```
init(project_path=apps/app)
  → nextjs_docs (after llms-index) for any API question
  → [user asked for dev] next dev on 3000
  → nextjs_index (port: "3000" if discovery fails)
  → nextjs_call get_errors | get_routes | get_project_metadata
```

Cache Components / PPR → `nextjs_docs` + optional MCP `enable_cache_components` — never enable from memory.

## Static gates (always — stop hook runs typecheck)

```bash
pnpm --filter app typecheck
pnpm --filter app test
pnpm check
```

## Completion checklist

- [ ] `init` called for this session
- [ ] Changed behavior verified against `nextjs_docs` (not memory)
- [ ] `pnpm --filter app typecheck` passes
- [ ] If dev server up: `get_errors` is clean
- [ ] No unsolicited `dev`/`build` (hook-enforced unless user asked)

## Scope

- App: `apps/app` (Next.js 16+, runtime MCP at `/_next/mcp`)
- Do not substitute MCP runtime checks with guesses about App Router or Cache Components
